result.execSummary:
The defendant Kyle E. BLAHA was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Deliver Methamphetamine(>3-10g), a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(e)2.
  • Possess Methamphetamine with intent to deliver (>10-50g), a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(e)3.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Amendment to Judgment of Conviction.
On 07-28-17, the court responded to a letter from Mr. Blaha sent requesting community service to repay his financial obligations.  He was advised to discuss this with his probation agent.  This agent spoke to him and found this to be a reasonable request.  On 10-29-17, Mr. Blaha completed 74 hours of community service at Grow It Forward.  Therefore, it is respectfully requested that his court costs be removed from his judgment of conviction.
(NOTE:  per Sec. 973.046 (1r), the DNA surcharge is not dischargeable through community service so that account remains due and owing. Agent notified via email.)
